video.title: Supergirl
video.synopsis: To avert a disaster, Kara Danvers reveals her powers and true identity: She is Superman's cousin, now known as Supergirl, protector of National City.

episodes.synopsis: While Kara Zor-El adapts to living in National City and working for media mogul Cat Grant, she can't turn away from her secret Kryptonian superpowers.
episodes.title: Pilot

episodes.synopsis: Kara's early forays into using her superpowers don't always go well. Cat's suspicions about Supergirl lead her to pressure James to get an exclusive.
episodes.title: Stronger Together

episodes.synopsis: Supergirl needs all her powers to battle Reactron, one of Superman's strongest foes. Cat's ongoing suspicion about Supergirl may lead to an expos√©.
episodes.title: Fight or Flight

episodes.synopsis: Kara's Thanksgiving is full of drama as her foster mother comes to town at the same time an accident turns a CatCo employee into the villain Livewire.
episodes.title: Livewire

episodes.synopsis: Kara must baby-sit Cat's son on the same day National City is rocked by a series of bombings needing Supergirl's attention. James's ex comes to town.
episodes.title: How Does She Do It?

episodes.synopsis: Kara's stress level goes off the charts during a training exercise commissioned by Gen. Sam Lane. Alex asks Winn to research her father's death.
episodes.title: Red Faced

episodes.synopsis: An earthquake cripples National City, leaving Kara and her friends without her superpowers. At the DEO, Alex's issues with Hank reach critical mass.
episodes.title: Human for a Day

episodes.synopsis: Kara is torn when Astra, her once-beloved aunt, challenges her belief in her mother. An email scandal at CatCo could spell the end of Cat's career.
episodes.title: Hostile Takeover

episodes.synopsis: Kara battles on two fronts when Cat becomes convinced her meek assistant is Supergirl at the same time Astra and Non are bent on Kara's destruction.
episodes.title: Blood Bonds

episodes.synopsis: Alex asks Hank to uncover Maxwell Lord's secret agenda. Cat offers Lucy a job, complicating things with James. Winn's father escapes from prison.
episodes.title: Childish Things

episodes.synopsis: When an anti-alien politician is kidnapped by a White Martian, Kara helps Hank confront his past. Kara encourages Cat to face her estranged older son.
episodes.title: Strange Visitor from Another Planet

episodes.synopsis: Supergirl fights against her own destruction by an evil doppelg√§nger. Cat's older son, Adam, and Kara are starting to have feelings for each other.
episodes.title: Bizarro

episodes.synopsis: A parasite traps Kara's mind inside a hallucination in which Krypton still exists. Hank and Alex must fend off an attack by Non without Supergirl.
episodes.title: For the Girl Who Has Everything

episodes.synopsis: Kara contends with a new back-stabbing assistant at CatCo. Supergirl confronts the Master Jailer. James questions the DEO, causing a rift with Kara.
episodes.title: Truth, Justice and The American Way

episodes.synopsis: Unsure how to defeat internet-traveler Indigo, Kara is counseled in Superman's Fortress of Solitude. James and Lucy rethink their relationship.
episodes.title: Solitude

episodes.synopsis: An encounter with Red Kryptonite turns sweet Kara evil, affecting her clothes and behavior at CatCo and the DEO. Alex and Lord become uneasy allies.
episodes.title: Falling

episodes.synopsis: Alex and Kara learn how Hank came to the DEO and his connection to their father. Kara binge eats as she tries to deal with the evil Supergirl fallout.
episodes.title: Manhunter

episodes.synopsis: Supergirl has an encounter with Flash, a speedy superhero from a parallel universe who helps her in exchange for assistance in getting him back home.
episodes.title: World's Finest

episodes.synopsis: Only Kara and Cat seem immune from Myriad, the mind control technique used by Non to turn National City's population into a zombie-like army.
episodes.title: Myriad

episodes.synopsis: To stop Non and Indigo's master plan to wipe out everyone on the planet, Supergirl is forced into a life or death battle against someone she loves.
episodes.title: Better Angels

episodes.synopsis: When a commercial space shuttle suffers engine failure, Kara's cousin Clark Kent is on hand to help her save the craft and investigate the incident.
episodes.title: The Adventures of Supergirl

episodes.synopsis: Supergirl is injured by a villain using kryptonite weapons to attack National City, and Superman places the blame squarely on Hank and the DEO.
episodes.title: The Last Children of Krypton

episodes.synopsis: Kara and the DEO fear that their escaped detainee is behind attacks on President Marsdin, who is visiting National City to sign an alien amnesty bill.
episodes.title: Welcome to Earth

episodes.synopsis: The corpse of an unregistered alien leads Kara to an underground "fight club" where aliens duel to the death under the supervision of Roulette.
episodes.title: Survivors

episodes.synopsis: When a gang of ruthless thieves using alien technology attacks Supergirl, she discovers that Cadmus is the source of their advanced weaponry.
episodes.title: Crossfire

episodes.synopsis: When J'onn and Kara are attacked by a scientist infected with an energy-draining parasite that saps their powers, the Guardian comes to their aid.
episodes.title: Changing

episodes.synopsis: On a mission to rescue Mon-El from Cadmus, Kara encounters the real Hank, who is now Cyborg Superman. The Guardian is falsely accused of murder.
episodes.title: The Darkest Place

episodes.synopsis: Kara tries to enlist Lena Luthor's help to prevent Cyborg Superman from releasing a Kryptonian virus that was created by her father, Zor-El.
episodes.title: Medusa

episodes.synopsis: Investigating a missing person case, Kara and Mon-El are transported to the slave planet Maaldoria, orbiting a red sun that robs them of their powers.
episodes.title: Supergirl Lives

episodes.synopsis: After a battle with Livewire, Kara is angry with Mon-El for ignoring her order to protect civilians, and with James, who reveals his secret identity.
episodes.title: We Can Be Heroes

episodes.synopsis: J'onn takes M'gann to the DEO for protection when her ex-lover Armek arrives on Earth to apprehend and return her to Mars for execution as a traitor.
episodes.title: The Martian Chronicles

episodes.synopsis: Refusing to believe that her friend is guilty, Kara tries to clear Lena's name when she is accused of helping Metallo and Lillian escape from prison.
episodes.title: Luthors

episodes.synopsis: When a trickster imp named Mxyzptlk appears with a marriage proposal for Kara, she and Mon-El must devise a way to stop the fifth-dimensional menace.
episodes.title: Mr. & Mrs. Mxzyptlk

episodes.synopsis: The Danvers family is thrilled when J'onn and Kara rescue Jeremiah from a Cadmus convoy, but Mon-El soon becomes suspicious of his sudden return.
episodes.title: Homecoming

episodes.synopsis: Kara pressures Snapper to run a story about Cadmus kidnapping aliens for relocation to another planet, while Alex and Maggie search for Jeremiah.
episodes.title: Exodus

episodes.synopsis: When the Daxamites demand the return of Mon-El to his home world, Kara discovers he is a prince who is expected to lead the rebuilding of his society.
episodes.title: Star-Crossed

episodes.synopsis: A series of attacks on Kara by alien bounty hunters leads Mon-El to suspect that his parents are behind them, in an effort to force him back to Daxam.
episodes.title: Distant Sun

episodes.synopsis: Lena's ex-boyfriend Jack announces a groundbreaking nanobot technology, but she, Kara and Mon-El discover that Jack is under his creation's power.
episodes.title: Ace Reporter

episodes.synopsis: A childhood friend of the Danverses who knows Kara's secret kidnaps Alex and demands that his father, a notorious criminal, be released from prison.
episodes.title: Alex

episodes.synopsis: When an alien from a normally peaceful race attacks National City, Kara, Mon-El and James discover a transporter created by Lena and the alien Rhea.
episodes.title: City of Lost Children

episodes.synopsis: The Daxamites invade National City, but Kara, Mon-El and their friends are able to turn the tide against Rhea, who unveils a startling secret weapon.
episodes.title: Resist

episodes.synopsis: With Kal restored to his normal state, Kara fights Rhea in an ancient combat ritual, while Lena works on a method of expelling the enemy fleet.
episodes.title: Nevertheless, She Persisted

episodes.synopsis: In the wake of the Daxamite invasion, Kara's still reeling from her sacrifice -- and a charismatic capitalist has big plans to rebuild National City.
episodes.title: Girl of Steel

episodes.synopsis: A powerful villain with psychic abilities brings Kara to her knees. Lena comes to work full time at CatCo and hands L-Corp over to a new successor.
episodes.title: Triggers

episodes.synopsis: With a wedding shower in the works, Maggie reaches out to her estranged father. Kara joins J'onn on an emotionally charged mission to Mars.
episodes.title: Far From the Tree

episodes.synopsis: A familiar symbol draws Kara to a man on a twisted mission. Samantha's leaning in at work but worries she's letting her daughter down.
episodes.title: The Faithful

episodes.synopsis: When lead poisoning hits National City's children, Morgan Edge goes public with a ruthless accusation. Alex and Maggie come to a painful realization.
episodes.title: Damage

episodes.synopsis: Kara takes Alex to Midvale for the weekend, where their childhood bedroom stirs memories of a painful tragedy that taught them to work as a team.
episodes.title: Midvale

episodes.synopsis: An underwater expedition awakens a long-buried hope. Samantha journeys home to investigate her past and unlocks the truth about her origin story.
episodes.title: Wake Up

episodes.synopsis: The Flash‚Äôs wedding draws Kara, Alex, Green Arrow and the Legends of Tomorrow to Central City, where a shadowy evil is waiting in the wings.
episodes.title: Crisis on Earth-X, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Lena and James team up to question Morgan Edge after ominous symbols appear in National City overnight. Christmas Eve delivers a dangerous new enemy.
episodes.title: Reign

episodes.synopsis: While Reign roams free in National City, Mon-El sends a member of the Legion of Super-Heroes into the depths of Kara's battered subconscious.
episodes.title: Legion of Super-Heroes

episodes.synopsis: Supergirl teams with Saturn Girl and a pair of unlikely allies on a mission to Fort Rozz to find a prisoner who knows how to defeat Reign.
episodes.title: Fort Rozz

episodes.synopsis: After an attempt on his life, Morgan Edge accuses Lena of foul play. Alex runs some tests to find the source of Samantha's blackouts.
episodes.title: For Good

episodes.synopsis: Kara's convinced that a captive Worldkiller still has some good in her, but Alex isn't buying it. Winn joins J'onn and Mon-El on an important mission.
episodes.title: Both Sides Now

episodes.synopsis: Winn reunites with his estranged mother, who reveals a surprising truth about his past. Alex senses something's off with Myr'nn's memory.
episodes.title: Schott Through the Heart

episodes.synopsis: A disturbance at the DEO forces J'onn to make a difficult decision. Mon-El starts training Kara in fighting techniques brought back from the future.
episodes.title: In Search of Lost Time

episodes.synopsis: A citywide plague points to Pestilence, but her identity's unknown. Lena and Samantha try to isolate the enzyme that triggers Reign's transformation.
episodes.title: Of Two Minds

episodes.synopsis: With all three Worldkillers united, Lena and Alex join forces with Supergirl to get through to Samantha in another dimension before time runs out.
episodes.title: Trinity

episodes.synopsis: Reign gains strength after absorbing the powers of Pestilence and Purity. Now she's more dangerous than ever -- and she's looking for Ruby.
episodes.title: Shelter from the Storm

episodes.synopsis: An escaped disciple of Coville's cult offers up a journal that could potentially save Sam. Someone threatens to reveal Guardian's identity.
episodes.title: The Fanatical

episodes.synopsis: Mon-El and Supergirl make a shocking discovery while carrying out an important mission. Back on Earth, Reign's wrath tests Lena's loyalties.
episodes.title: Dark Side of the Moon

episodes.synopsis: Kara weighs a life-altering decision with major repercussions for her friends on Earth. James and J'onn trace the source of a superpowered weapon.
episodes.title: Not Kansas

episodes.synopsis: Supergirl, Mon-El and Alura join forces to stop Selena as she heads toward Earth with a sinister plan. J‚Äôonn prepares for an important goodbye.
episodes.title: Make It Reign

episodes.synopsis: With Earth in turmoil, the team bands together to fight Reign, forcing Supergirl to question what she stands for. A weakened Sam searches for strength.
episodes.title: Battles Lost and Won

episodes.synopsis: J'onn tries to convince Kara that the climate toward aliens is changing. A new cub reporter comes to CatCo, and Lena reconnects with her mother.
episodes.title: American Alien

episodes.synopsis: A shocking revelation stirs anger and resentment while Mercy Graves remains at large. Nia confides in James, and L-Corp comes under attack.
episodes.title: Fallout

episodes.synopsis: A flashback episode reveals Agent Liberty's origins, tracing his dark rise from a college professor to a villain fueled by anti-alien rage.
episodes.title: Man of Steel

episodes.synopsis: With the air still awash in dangerous kryptonite, multiple heroes put their lives on the line. J‚Äôonn's search for Fiona turns up a sympathetic ally.
episodes.title: Ahimsa

episodes.synopsis: Agent Liberty gains an alarming new weapon in his warped war to "save" humanity. J'onn and Kara work together to recover a powerful amulet.
episodes.title: Parasite Lost

episodes.synopsis: With Thanksgiving approaching, Agent Liberty spreads his manifesto of hate as James, Alex and Kara race to thwart a wave of anti-alien violence.
episodes.title: Call to Action

episodes.synopsis: Things take a dark turn when Supergirl and Manchester Black follow a lead on Agent Liberty's location. Lena launches her first set of trials.
episodes.title: Rather the Fallen Angel

episodes.synopsis: After Nia shares a prophetic dream, Kara and Brainy encourage her to embrace her destiny. A vengeful Manchester Black pays Ben Lockwood a visit.
episodes.title: Bunker Hill

episodes.synopsis: Supergirl teams with the Flash, Green Arrow and Superman on a crossover mission to find an important book and rewrite a scrambled reality.
episodes.title: Elseworlds: Hour Three

episodes.synopsis: Col. Haley makes it her mission to uncover Supergirl's secret identity, but Alex is determined to protect her. Brainy urges Nia to use her gifts.
episodes.title: Suspicious Minds

episodes.synopsis: A new drug on the streets of National City gives ordinary people temporary superpowers. Kara accompanies Nia on a trip home to visit her family.
episodes.title: Blood Memory

episodes.synopsis: Valentine's Day takes a detour as J'onn and Kara dig into a case that's connected to a grisly DEO investigation -- and a frightening new villain.
episodes.title: Menagerie

episodes.synopsis: Manchester Black springs back into action with a newly formed team of allies known as "The Elite." Elsewhere, Nia doubles down on her training.
episodes.title: What's So Funny About Truth, Justice and the American Way?

episodes.synopsis: With human-alien tensions at an all-time high, Supergirl is forced to take a stand to keep the peace. A difficult assignment tests Alex's beliefs.
episodes.title: Stand and Deliver

episodes.synopsis: Lex Luthor pays Lena a visit -- and preys upon her sympathies. With James's life hanging in the balance, J'onn and Kara go after Manchester Black.
episodes.title: O Brother, Where Art Thou?

episodes.synopsis: Flashbacks reveal that Lex Luthor's return was all part of a much larger plan involving Lena, Kara -- and a dangerously powerful lookalike.
episodes.title: The	House of L

episodes.synopsis: With Lex Luthor still at large, Supergirl, Alex and Lena go after his most loyal henchwoman. A troubled J'onn summons his father's spirit.
episodes.title: All About Eve

episodes.synopsis: Lena and Supergirl search Stryker's Island for clues that might lead them to Lex. James goes to therapy, and Brainy has a crisis of conscience.
episodes.title: Crime and Punishment

episodes.synopsis: Dreamer steps forward to protect the city while Kara works to expose Lex -- and clear Supergirl's name. James confronts his core trauma.
episodes.title: American Dreamer

episodes.synopsis: The search for Lex leads Kara and Lena to Kaznia, where shocking surprises await. A grieving Lockwood takes comfort in revenge.
episodes.title: Will the Real Miss Tessmacher Please Stand Up?

episodes.synopsis: Kara comes face-to-face with Red Daughter. Elsewhere, Brainy leads an alien rescue mission, and Lockwood learns the truth about Lex.
episodes.title: Red Dawn

episodes.synopsis: Lex summons Lena and Lillian to the White House, then suits up to fight Supergirl in an epic battle with earthly consequences.
episodes.title: The Quest for Peace

episodes.synopsis: Stung by Kara's lies, Lena contemplates revenge. CatCo undergoes a journalistic shift. Supergirl suffers a suit mishap while battling a mysterious foe.
episodes.title: Event Horizon

episodes.synopsis: J'onn searches for answers after a jarring Martian encounter. Lena explores the limits of Obsidian's new technology. A brash colleague undermines Kara.
episodes.title: Stranger Beside Me

episodes.synopsis: Kara attempts to make amends with Lena amid a murder investigation. J'onn uncovers a tragic piece of his past. Kelly's compassion puts her in danger.
episodes.title: Blurred Lines

episodes.synopsis: As the DEO searches for a way to capture Malefic, Kara digs deeper into William's suspicious activities, and James and Kelly return to their hometown.
episodes.title: In Plain Sight

episodes.synopsis: Kara assists William with his investigation as a supervillain tied to his past resurfaces ahead of Obsidian's VR launch. Lena makes a dangerous deal.
episodes.title: Dangerous Liaisons

episodes.synopsis: The supervillain's detention at the DEO sets off a chain of events that links back to Lena's long-ago first encounter with Andrea.
episodes.title: Confidence Women

episodes.synopsis: When an ancient power targets Lena, Supergirl finally discovers the cold hard truth about their friendship. J'onn comes to a decision about Malefic.
episodes.title: Tremors

episodes.synopsis: Supergirl must decide whether to listen to her heart or her head when it comes to Lena. Meanwhile, the threat from Leviathan erupts thanks to Rama Khan.
episodes.title: The Wrath of Rama Khan

episodes.synopsis: Facing an imminent cataclysm amid a devastating personal loss, Supergirl joins her fellow superheroes in a heroic final stand to save the planet.
episodes.title: Crisis on Infinite Earths: Hour One

episodes.synopsis: It's a whole new reality on post-Crisis Earth, where Kara finds some changes tough to swallow, and Brainy sees he's not living up to his full potential.
episodes.title: The Bottle Episode

episodes.synopsis: An old friend returns to take down his evil doppelg√§nger. Brainy questions his current path. Kara tries to protect Will from Lex Luthor‚Äôs wrath.
episodes.title: Back from the Future: Part One

episodes.synopsis: Supergirl partners with Winn on a high-tech mission at the DEO. Brainy's endgame with Lex grows increasingly at odds with his allegiance to his friends.
episodes.title: Back from the Future: Part Two

episodes.synopsis: A banished Mr. Mxyzptlk reappears, offering Kara the chance to travel through time, make different choices and repair her fractured friendship with Lena.
episodes.title: It's a Super Life

episodes.synopsis: Lex assigns Supergirl to protection duty when Andrea gets attacked ahead of Obsidian's big VR launch. Lena finds willing subjects to test Non Nocere.
episodes.title: The Bodyguard

episodes.synopsis: Dreamer vows to exact justice after a friend becomes the target of a transphobic attack. Alex enters the virtual world in search of a missing person.
episodes.title: Reality Bytes

episodes.synopsis: The lines of reality begin to blur when Alex takes on a powerful new identity inside Obsidian's virtual world. Kara deals with a devastating loss.
episodes.title: Alex in Wonderland

episodes.synopsis: As Lex Luthor's post-Crisis game plan finally comes to fruition, his labyrinthian schemes to thwart his enemies and secure his power are revealed.
episodes.title: Deus Lex Machina

episodes.synopsis: While Supergirl and her friends take on a Leviathan power player, Lena teams up with Lex after a Non Nocere glitch lands them in jeopardy.
episodes.title: The Missing Link

episodes.synopsis: Kara relies on her friends ‚Äî both current and former ‚Äî to help her save the world when Lex's sinister plan with Leviathan inches toward checkmate.
episodes.title: Immortal Kombat

episodes.synopsis: Kara and her friends join forces to stop Lex Luthor when his latest plan for world domination makes him a more powerful threat than they ever imagined.
episodes.title: Rebirth

episodes.synopsis: Trials and tribulations lie ahead for Kara and her team as they fight to keep hope alive against impossible odds. Lena risks everything to take on Lex.
episodes.title: A Few Good Women

episodes.synopsis: An injured Kara meets a new friend. Lena and Brainy hit their limit with Lex's cat-and-mouse games. Alex and J'onn deal with their complicated emotions.
episodes.title: Phantom Menaces

episodes.synopsis: Kara closes in on a possible escape from the Phantom Zone, while Lena's mission with the Super Friends makes her question if she's where she belongs.
episodes.title: Lost Souls

episodes.synopsis: Brainy and Nia time-travel back to 2009 to find Kara's DNA at her hometown high school, but their daring mission quickly veers off course.
episodes.title: Prom Night

episodes.synopsis: With the timeline in disarray, Brainy and Nia scramble to put things right on prom night amid alien abductors, meteors and an inquisitive Cat Grant.
episodes.title: Prom Again!

episodes.synopsis: Kara's friends confront their darkest, most deep-seated fears during a nightmarish rescue mission to the Phantom Zone.
episodes.title: Fear Knot

episodes.synopsis: Kara tries to put her time in the Phantom Zone behind her, but memories haunt her as she returns to life as a reporter and superhero in National City.
episodes.title: Welcome Back, Kara!

episodes.synopsis: Kara teams up with Kelly to help a troubled young alien orphan who's worried about his imprisoned big brother. Nyxly infiltrates Nia's dreams.
episodes.title: Dream Weaver

episodes.synopsis: As Kara fights to save an affordable housing program, Nia receives some tough love after her deal with Nyxly, and Kelly begins her Guardian training.
episodes.title: Still I Rise

episodes.synopsis: Mxy returns and serenades Kara and friends with an anthemic song about Nyxly's past. Lena visits Newfoundland to learn more about her mother's past.
episodes.title: Mxy in the Middle

episodes.synopsis: Stepping into her role as Guardian, Kelly seeks assistance from her friends after a building collapse but soon realizes they don't see the bigger issues.
episodes.title: Blindspots

episodes.synopsis: When a magical totem splits in half during a museum heist, Kara and Nyxly must undergo tests of courage to gain full control of the artifact.
episodes.title: The Gauntlet

episodes.synopsis: Kara wants Lena to use her budding powers to help nab a totem from an overemotional Nyxly. William begins his new newsbeat with the Super Friends.
episodes.title: Magical Thinking

episodes.synopsis: Kara continues to battle Nyxly for the remaining totems, while Alex and Kelly face their biggest ‚Äî and most exciting ‚Äî challenge as a couple.
episodes.title: Hope for Tomorrow

episodes.synopsis: Kara begins to question her double life as a superhero and reporter, and Nia's search for the dream totem leads to a run-in with her estranged sister.
episodes.title: A Nightmare in National City

episodes.synopsis: As Lex Luthor works to win over Nyxly, Kara and her friends set a trap with a totem while Alex prepares to ask Kelly an all-important question.
episodes.title: Believe in a Thing Called Love

episodes.synopsis: With Nyxly and Lex plotting over the totems, Kara offers Alex advice about Esme, Brainy receives devastating news and William feels betrayed by Andrea.
episodes.title: Truth or Consequences

episodes.synopsis: As a loved one's life hangs in the balance, Kara and friends contemplate a drastic course of action to keep the totems out of Lex and Nyxly's hands.
episodes.title: The Last Gauntlet

episodes.synopsis: Allies from the past jump in to help the Super Friends battle Lex and Nyxly as Kara reconsiders her future and Alex and Kelly prepare to tie the knot.
episodes.title: Kara
